  "subject": "Move property names to Operator",
  "commit_message": "Move property names to Operator\n\nWhen an Operation is constructed, it assumes that the ControlLoopParams\nis fully populated.  However, the data may not all be available until\ngetPropertyNames() has been called and the preprocessing steps executed.\nThis creates a catch-22 situation.  Solved the problem by moving the\ngetPropertyNames() method from the Operation class to the Operator class.\nAlso fixed a case in A&AI post-processing steps to prevent NPE when\nthe event context is not provided.\n\nIssue-ID: POLICY-2746\nChange-Id: I2595ba83f181c6028b93ce6817744b9c37eb44c5\nSigned-off-by: Jim Hahn <jrh3@att.com>\n",
